	abstract = {* •Although there is unambiguous evidence for vascular epiphytic plants to be limited by insufficient water and nutrient supply under natural conditions, it is an open debate whether they are primarily phosphorus (P) or nitrogen (N) limited.
* •Plant 15N fractionation and foliar N : P stoichiometry of a tank epiphyte (Vriesea sanguinolenta), and its response to combined N–P fertilization, were studied under semi-natural conditions over 334 d to clarify the type of nutrient limitation.
